{# Phase 14 SB4 Slice 4 Task 4.2: lazy journal-listing thumbnail fragment. The
   ONLY | safe content is matplotlib-generated SVG bytes. Operator/derived text
   is auto-escaped. Fragment root is a <svg>/<span> (never a bare <tr>), so the
   HTMX synthetic-table-wrap hazard does not apply.

   The busy state is transient render backpressure: the cell's `revealed`
   trigger already fired, so a busy fragment that did not re-trigger would
   strand the thumbnail until a full table rerender. The busy span SELF-RETRIES
   with a bounded backoff delay (hx-target=this / hx-swap=outerHTML REPLACES the
   busy span, never nests the SVG inside it) so it recovers to the SVG once the
   render semaphore frees. #}
{% if chart_svg_bytes %}{{ chart_svg_bytes.decode('utf-8') | safe }}
{% elif not_found %}<span class="chart-unavailable" data-chart-reason="trade-not-found">Trade not found.</span>
{% elif busy %}<span class="chart-unavailable" data-chart-reason="busy"
      hx-get="/journal/trades/{{ trade_id }}/thumbnail"
      hx-trigger="load delay:1500ms" hx-target="this" hx-swap="outerHTML"
      hx-headers='{"HX-Request": "true"}'>Chart loading...</span>
{% else %}<span class="chart-unavailable" data-chart-reason="no-coverage">Chart unavailable.</span>{% endif %}
